                <p>Surname from first <term ref="#t822" type="subject">husband</term>: <persName ref="#ehri_et_zigelman_marta" type="ehri">Zigelman,
                        Marta</persName></p>
                <p>Testimony taken by <persName ref="#ehri_et_mamet_p" type="ehri">P. Mamet</persName>, <date when="1946-08-04">4.8.1946</date></p>
                <p>Liquidation of the Jews of <placeName ref="#belzyce" type="ehri">Bełżyce</placeName></p>
                <p>Until the outbreak of the <term ref="#t1080" type="subject">war</term> in <date when="1939">1939</date>, I lived in <placeName
                        ref="#lublin" type="ehri">Lublin</placeName>. In fall <date when="1940">1940</date>, all Jews were <term ref="#t518"
                        type="subject">deported</term> from <placeName ref="#lublin" type="ehri">Lublin</placeName> by the <term
                        ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> and settled in the villages surrounding <placeName ref="#lublin"
                        type="ehri">Lublin</placeName>. The <term ref="#t518" type="subject">deported</term> Jews would be taken on <term ref="#t940"
                        type="subject">wagon</term>s, frequently they would be driven en masse on foot, very often it would happen during such a <term
                        ref="#t518" type="subject">deportation</term> that many succumbed. I, my <term ref="#t822" type="subject">husband</term>, and
                    my two <term ref="#t822" type="subject">sons</term> aged 12–13 were <term ref="#t518" type="subject">deported</term> to <placeName
                        ref="#lubartow" type="ehri">Lubartów</placeName> near <placeName ref="#lublin" type="ehri">Lublin</placeName>. I tore myself
                        <term ref="#t204" type="subject">away</term> from the entire <term ref="#t521" type="subject">transport</term> and went back
                    to my home in <placeName ref="#lublin" type="ehri">Lublin</placeName>, and I <term ref="#t262" type="subject">hid</term> there in
                    the <term ref="#t265" type="subject">attic</term>. My <term ref="#t822" type="subject">husband</term> and <term ref="#t822"
                        type="subject">children</term> were taken to <placeName ref="#lubartow" type="ehri">Lubartów</placeName>. My <term ref="#t822"
                        type="subject">brother</term>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_veisbrod_leibush" type="ehri">Veisbrod Leibush</persName>, was living
                    at that time in <placeName ref="#belzyce" type="ehri">Bełżyce</placeName> near <placeName ref="#lublin" type="ehri"
                        >Lublin</placeName> – I called him on the telephone [to ask] that he should send a <term ref="#t940" type="subject"
                        >wagon</term> for me, and so I arrived in <placeName ref="#belzyce" type="ehri">Bełżyce</placeName>. In <placeName
                        ref="#belzyce" type="ehri">Bełżyce</placeName> I gathered together a few <term ref="#t1207" type="subject">people</term> and
                    organized a [public] <term ref="#t832" type="subject">kitchen</term>, where the <term ref="#t519" type="subject">deportees</term>
                    and the poor <term ref="#t1207" type="subject">people</term> of <placeName ref="#belzyce" type="ehri">Bełżyce</placeName> would
                    come to eat. We <term ref="#t832" type="subject">fed</term> around 1200 to 1500 <term ref="#t1207" type="subject">people</term>.
                    Also here I want to relate to what extent the <term ref="#t1181" type="subject">German regime</term> was rotten, that we could
                    persuade the most important among them of anything for [the price of] <term ref="#t1053" type="subject">gold or valuables</term>.
                    Near us was <persName ref="#ehri_et_standartenfuehrer_stemmler" type="ehri">Standartenführer Stemmler</persName>, we could <term
                        ref="#t1053" type="subject">bribe</term> him with hard/heavy gold and diamonds as well as fabric and boots – redeeming Jews
                    from the <term ref="#t567" type="subject">camp</term> of <placeName ref="#l1692" type="camp">Józefów</placeName> near <placeName
                        ref="#l565" type="camp">Pulawy</placeName>, not far from <placeName ref="#warsaw" type="ehri">Warsaw</placeName> – from <term
                        ref="#t745" type="subject">death</term>. As a result of our acquaintance with the <term ref="#t873" type="subject">Jewish
                        representatives</term>, such as <persName ref="#ehri_et_feltscher" type="ehri">Dr. Feltscher</persName>, the <orgName
                        ref="#g429" type="ehri">SS</orgName> men <persName ref="#ehri_et_kranbuegel" type="ehri">Kranbuegel</persName> and <persName
                        ref="#ehri_et_engel" type="ehri">Engel</persName>, who were considered the most famous <term ref="#t477" type="subject">camp
                        directors</term> in <placeName ref="#republic-of-poland" type="ehri">Poland</placeName> – until <date when="1942">1942</date>
                    we were able for various prices to ensure that no</p>
                <pb facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540315_02.jpg" n="2"/>
                <p><term ref="#t545" type="subject">ghetto</term> or <term ref="#t567" type="subject">camp</term> would be established in our city
                        (<placeName ref="#belzyce" type="ehri">Bełżyce</placeName>). Nevertheless in <date when="1942">1942</date>, in the eighth
                    month, a Jewish quarter [city] was established in our town. They <term ref="#t614" type="subject">gathered</term> all the Jews
                    from the entire <placeName ref="#lublin" type="ehri">Lublin</placeName> district – they deceived them and told them to bring
                    everything with them – it was pitiful to see how the Jews even dragged with them wood. In this way, with us in <placeName
                        ref="#belzyce" type="ehri">Bełżyce</placeName> were <term ref="#t614" type="subject">gathered</term> together around 9000
                    Jews. They allowed them to rest for three days – on the third day, the <orgName ref="#g429" type="ehri">SS</orgName> man inspector
                        <persName ref="#ehri_et_engel" type="ehri">Engel</persName> entered the Jewish quarter – this was a beast in the form of a
                        <term ref="#t826" type="subject">man</term> – straight away in the square he <term ref="#t540" type="subject">murdered</term>
                    700 <term ref="#t1207" type="subject">people</term> – the rest were taken away to <placeName ref="#l41" type="camp"
                        >Bełżec </placeName>near <placeName ref="#tomaszow-lubelski" type="ehri">Tomaszów</placeName>. There they <term ref="#t516"
                        type="subject">burned</term> them in the <term ref="#t501" type="subject">crematoria</term>.</p>
                <p>There remained Jews in <term ref="#t262" type="subject">hiding</term>, who had <term ref="#t262" type="subject">hidden</term> in
                    the city and the surrounding forests and came back after the <term ref="#t550" type="subject">aktion</term> – around 600 <term
                        ref="#t1207" type="subject">persons</term>. From these <term ref="#t1207" type="subject">people</term> a <term ref="#t567"
                        type="subject">camp</term> was created in <placeName ref="#belzyce" type="ehri">Bełżyce</placeName> – our <term ref="#t567"
                        type="subject">camp</term> was directed by the <orgName ref="#g429" type="ehri">SS</orgName> men <persName
                        ref="#ehri_et_engel" type="ehri">Engel</persName> and Yakab.<note place="bottom">Spelling uncertain - Vakab? Yakab?</note>
                    <orgName ref="#g512" type="ehri">The camp committee</orgName> and the police were Jews. <term ref="#t1207" type="subject"
                        >People</term> worked at hacking stones, building highways, for the firm Keymer. On <date when="1943-05-08">8.V.1943</date>,
                    some of the <term ref="#t1207" type="subject">people</term> from the <term ref="#t567" type="subject">camp</term> were <term
                        ref="#t532" type="subject">murdered</term> and a few, even before this when they saw that a <term ref="#t567" type="subject"
                        >camp</term> was created, <term ref="#t204" type="subject">fled</term> from <placeName ref="#belzyce" type="ehri"
                        >Bełżyce</placeName> via various means. I myself left <placeName ref="#belzyce" type="ehri">Bełżyce</placeName> in the
                    following way. At 3 AM I went out with my <term ref="#t822" type="subject">son</term>, who was sick with <term ref="#t493"
                        type="subject">typhus</term>, running with him to the wires of the <term ref="#t567" type="subject">camp</term>.</p>
                <pb facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540315_03.jpg" n="3"/>
                <p>I <term ref="#t204" type="subject">cut through</term> the wires and set out for <placeName ref="#warsaw" type="ehri"
                        >Warsaw</placeName>. On <date when="1943-05-05">V.5.1943</date>, I arrived in <placeName ref="#warsaw" type="ehri"
                        >Warsaw</placeName>. The news that the <term ref="#t567" type="subject">camp</term> had been decimated was brought to me
                    already in <placeName ref="#warsaw" type="ehri">Warsaw</placeName> by my <term ref="#t822" type="subject">brother</term>. I want
                    just to mention here the <term ref="#t567" type="subject">camp</term> director of <placeName ref="#belzyce" type="ehri"
                        >Bełżyce</placeName> by the name <persName ref="#p000154" type="ehri">Göth</persName> – he <term ref="#t532" type="subject"
                        >murdered</term> a few hundred <term ref="#t824" type="subject">children</term> in the following manner – he gathered them all
                    together, took them to the <term ref="#t747" type="subject">cemetery</term>, ordered the <term ref="#t824" type="subject"
                        >children</term> to undress, lined them up naked in a row, and, with a cruel, cold-bloodedness <term ref="#t540"
                        type="subject">shot</term> them all. One young <term ref="#t824" type="subject">boy</term>, his name was <persName
                        ref="#ehri_et_kuropotvo" type="ehri">Kuropotvo</persName>, <term ref="#t262" type="subject">hid</term> among the <term
                        ref="#t532" type="subject">dead</term>
                    <term ref="#t824" type="subject">children</term> and came to the city the next day, early in the morning, covered in blood,
                    because the bullet did not hit him, and he told me the entire story. The day after the <term ref="#t824" type="subject"
                        >children</term> were taken away, the <term ref="#t567" type="subject">camp</term> director <persName ref="#p000154"
                        type="ehri">Goth</persName>, who was also one of the <term ref="#t567" type="subject">camp</term> directors with whom we were
                    acquainted and whom we would <term ref="#t1053" type="subject">bribe</term>, told us, <q>I have taken good care of all the <term
                            ref="#t824" type="subject">children</term> – I brought them all to <placeName ref="#poniatowa" type="ehri"
                            >Poniatowa</placeName> near <placeName ref="#lublin" type="ehri">Lublin</placeName>!</q> – The young <term ref="#t824"
                        type="subject">boy</term>
                    <persName ref="#ehri_et_kuropotvo" type="ehri">Kuropotvo</persName> who avoided <term ref="#t745" type="subject">death</term> at
                    the hands of <persName ref="#p000154" type="ehri">Göth</persName> fell during a later <term ref="#t550" type="subject"
                        >aktion</term>. The <term ref="#t824" type="subject">children’s</term>
                    <term ref="#t550" type="subject">aktion</term> during which <persName ref="#p000154" type="ehri">Göth</persName>
                    <term ref="#t532" type="subject">murdered</term> them took place in <date when="1943-03">March 1943</date> in <placeName
                        ref="#belzyce" type="ehri">Bełżyce</placeName>. <persName ref="#ehri_et_rubinstyn_marta" type="ehri">Marta
                        Rubinstyn</persName>.</p>
